Vice President Mike Pence delivers remarks at the Marine Barracks in Washington, D.C. to commemorate the 34th anniversary of the Beirut Marine barracks bombing. He expresses condolences to the families of those who lost loved ones in the attack and honors the service and sacrifice of the fallen. Pence also discusses the ongoing fight against terrorism and emphasizes the Trump administration's commitment to supporting the military and defeating the enemy. He highlights the recent liberation of Raqqa from ISIS and the determination to continue hunting down and destroying the terrorist group. Pence concludes by sharing a personal story about his brother, who was a Marine stationed in Beirut at the time of the bombing. He pledges to never forget the fallen and to honor their service by keeping the flame of freedom alive.